================================================================================
  4. SIGNIFICANT BUSINESS PROCESS EXCEPTION
================================================================================

4.1 Scope. The Workflow Service Restriction in Section 3 does NOT apply when
    workflow provisioning is a component of a Significant Business Process
    (Section 1.7), not the primary product itself.

4.2 Permitted Activities Under This Exception. If Your product qualifies as
    a Significant Business Process, You may:

    (a) Use all VSAL-covered components internally, including Provisionable
        Mode, to orchestrate Your own business logic.
    (b) Expose Your product to customers through any interface (web, mobile,
        API), even if customer actions trigger workflow execution internally.
    (c) Accept structured customer input (forms, uploads, API payloads) that
        Your predefined workflows process — this is data flow, not workflow
        provisioning.
    (d) Allow customers to configure domain-specific business rules within
        Your product's fixed domain model (e.g., credit policy thresholds,
        routing rules, approval chains) — this is configuration, not
        workflow definition upload.
    (e) Distribute the Software to clients who deploy it themselves on their
        own infrastructure — this is software distribution, not a managed
        service.

4.3 Examples of Permitted Use:

    - A credit scoring platform using workflows to orchestrate scoring.
    - An IoT monitoring platform routing sensor data through workflows.
    - A payment processing system managing transaction routing.
    - An insurance underwriting system orchestrating risk assessment.
    - An e-commerce platform managing order fulfillment.
    - A healthcare integration platform connecting hospital systems.
    - A telehealth platform orchestrating appointment / triage / prescription.
    - A logistics platform handling route optimization and customs clearance.
    - A banking core handling AML, transaction posting, reconciliation.
    - A KYC / compliance SaaS running verification and sanctions screening.
    - An HR platform orchestrating application screening and onboarding.
    - A manufacturing MES coordinating machines and quality control.
    - A government e-service routing permit applications and approval chains.
    - A learning management system handling enrollment and certification.

4.4 The Test. Ask: "If workflow provisioning capability were removed from
    our product, would the product still deliver substantial value?" If
    yes, the product qualifies under this exception. The workflow engine
    is an implementation detail, not the product.

4.5 The Distinguishing Line. Customers of a Significant Business Process
    USE Your product (submit data, configure domain rules, consume
    results). Customers of Workflow-as-a-Service UPLOAD workflow
    definitions. If Your customers' interaction is limited to Your
    product's domain model, You are permitted under this exception even
    if internally You use Provisionable Mode to iterate faster.


